<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-17T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-17T07:00:00-05:00" n="453" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">837.01/34: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                            Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-17T09:00:00-03:00">October 17, 1933—9
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>93. Minister for Foreign Affairs tells me Argentine Ambassador
                                yesterday urged that the time had come for the South American states
                                to agree as to recognition of government in Cuba. He was told
                                reports just received from Brazilian Legation were distinctly
                                discouraging and that Brazilian Government would await more
                                favorable developments.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>